==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Capitulary
<hw>Ca*pit"u*la*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Capitularies</plw> <pr>(#)</pr></plu>. <ety>[See
<er>Capitular</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A capitular.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The body of laws or statutes of a chapter, or of an
ecclesiastical council.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A collection of laws or statutes, civil and
ecclesiastical, esp. of the Frankish kings, in chapters or
sections.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Several of Charlemagne's <qex>capitularies</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Hallam.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

